            <p>With a lower price point than Dyson but nevertheless powerful suction and versatility, the Shark Vertex is an attractive option for shoppers who are looking for a tough cordless vacuum that won’t break the bank. With an impressive 281 AW of suction power and a 60-minute battery life, not to mention a wide assortment of included attachments, the Shark Vertex is a strong contender. Some drawbacks of the Vertex include its small dust bin capacity, which may need to be emptied often for larger cleaning jobs, as well a relatively high noise level. However, a 5-year limited warranty can certainly sweeten the deal.</p>

