            <div class="BestList-container BestList-buyersGuide" id="buyers-guide">
                <h2 class="BestList-guide center title-2">Buyer&#x27;s Guide</h2>
                <div class="RichTextBody body-1">
                    <ps-toggler data-toggle="review" class="ToggleText " itemprop="description" data-fade-out="true">
    
        <div data-toggle-content
            data-size="large"
            class="ToggleText-content body-1">
            <p>Some helpful tips for buyers, along with some context for our recommendations.</p><h3>Factors We Considered in Our Cordless Vacuum Reviews</h3><p></p><p>In this review, we took a look at our top five cordless vacuums, which we have evaluated taking the following factors into account:</p><h4>Cleaning Ability</h4><p></p><p>It's essential to think about the surfaces you'll be cleaning and the use cases you have in mind. Are you looking for a <a class="Link" href="https://www.latimes.com/bestcovery/best-robot-vacuum" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">vacuum</a> that's best for hard floors, carpets, or a mixture of both? Does it clean upholstery? Does it handle smaller, more delicate surfaces? Do you need a vacuum for pet hair, or are you looking for something that can handle heavy debris?</p><h4>Comfort and Ease</h4><p></p><p>Is this vacuum convenient and easy to use? How lightweight and nimble is the vacuum? A vacuum that's too heavy or cumbersome to maneuver around your home won't be of much use, no matter how well it cleans. We also consider the vacuum's ergonomics and the quality of the handle and controls to ensure that you can use it comfortably for extended periods.</p><h4>Battery Life and Runtime</h4><p></p><p>We pay close attention to the battery life of each vacuum we review. We consider whether the vacuum has any battery-saving features, such as a "power save" mode or a "low battery" indicator.</p><h4>Weight, Size, and Bin Capacity</h4><p></p><p>A vacuum that's too large or heavy to carry around your home will quickly become a hassle, while a vacuum with a small bin capacity may need to be emptied frequently. When evaluating the best handheld vacuums, we look for vacuums that are the right size, weight, and capacity for the typical person's needs.</p><h4>Warranties</h4><p></p><p>The warranties offered by each vacuum manufacturer also play a part in our recommendations. The better the warranty, the more peace of mind you get for the quality of your purchase.</p><h4>Suction Power</h4><p></p><p>The maneuverability of wireless vacuums can sometimes come at the cost of suction power. That makes it important to look for one with higher suction power, ensuring you have the power you need to clear dust and dirt effectively.</p><h4>Extras</h4><p></p><p>We also look at the extras and special features or attachments that each vacuum comes with, such as crevice attachments, motorized brush rolls, HEPA filtration, and more.</p><h4>Price</h4><p></p><p>Finally, we evaluate each vacuum based on price, as this allows you to take a closer look at what the product offers and determine for yourself if it's still a good value for you at that price point.</p><h3><b>Benefits of Going Cordless</b></h3><p></p><p><i><b>Convenience:</b></i> Since cordless vacuums don't need to be plugged in while you clean and tend to be lightweight and nimble, they tend to be much more convenient for regular use. That means quick clean-ups are simpler, not requiring you to lug a heavy machine out of the closet and painstakingly unravel a long, tangling electrical cord. Cordless vacuums are incredibly convenient to use. They are lightweight, easy to maneuver, and don't require you to plug them in. This makes them perfect for quick clean-ups and spot cleaning.</p><p><i><b>Versatility:</b></i> Portable vacuums tend to also be "stick" vacuums. Their long and slender designs make cleaning tight or out-of-reach areas easier. These vacuums also tend to come with an assortment of tools and attachments, allowing users to clean more surfaces than just hardwood and carpeting.</p><p><i><b>Portability:</b></i> The lightweight and battery power of a cordless vacuum makes it incredibly portable. Cordless models remove the need to shuffle from power outlet to power outlet for larger cleaning jobs, and if you need to clean on multiple floors of your home, they are easily carried up and down stairs. Their compact designs also make it easier to transport handheld vacuums in your car or even to clean the car itself.</p><p><i><b>Quiet:</b></i> The best cordless vacuums also have a considerably lower volume than traditional vacuums, making them a more attractive option if you need to clean in the other room while someone in your home is sleeping or studying.</p><h3><b>How to Choose Which One Is Best for You</b></h3><p></p><p>The most important consideration when deciding on a cordless vacuum is your personal use case. What kind of messes do you routinely need to clean up? Which surfaces do your messes tend to occur on, and how often do you need to pull out your vacuum cleaner to spot clean?</p><p>Once you understand your home's cleaning needs, you can start researching the features, tools, and specs of different models. Based on your most common tasks and cleaning needs, which model meets most of your needs and includes the attachments that make those jobs easier? Use those features to narrow your search down to a handful of models.</p><p>With a few promising options in front of you, it's time to consider the price. Looking at the models that meet your needs should give you a good idea of the price range for the quality of vacuum cleaner you need. While understanding that you sometimes get what you pay for, do your best to find the selections with the best value, and don't be afraid to hunt for deals.</p><p>Narrowing your selections a little further by price, it's time to look at customer reviews. Finding legitimate, unbiased reviews of how the vacuum performs in the real world is a great way to gauge the performance of each model, allowing you to see how customers like yourself fared after buying the vacuum you're considering.</p><h2>FAQ</h2><p></p><p>These are some of the most common questions that consumers ask about cordless vacuums.</p><p><b>Are expensive vacuums worth it?</b></p><p>Though some can certainly be overpriced, the fact of the matter is that vacuum cleaners are one of those areas where you truly get what you pay for. It's tempting to buy a cheaper vacuum and be done with it, but bargain models don't tend to be built to last. So, in the long run, you'll end up spending more by replacing your cheaper vacuum cleaner every year or two.</p><p><b>How long should my vacuum last?</b></p><p>The lifespan of a cordless vacuum can vary significantly depending on the type and quality of the machine. For all of their advantages, one potential drawback for cordless vacuums is that they tend to have shorter lifespans than corded models. Generally, cordless vacuums can last anywhere from two to five years, with higher-quality models typically outlasting bargain vacuums.</p><p><b>What features should I look for in a cordless vacuum?</b></p><p>When choosing a rechargeable vacuum, consider the following factors:</p><p><i><b>Battery life:</b></i> A longer battery life is ideal, so you don't have to worry about recharging while cleaning.</p><p><i><b>Suction power:</b></i> Look for a vacuum with strong suction power, often measured in air watts (AW), to pick up dirt, dust, and debris effectively.</p><p><i><b>Weight:</b></i> A lightweight and easy-to-maneuver vacuum will make cleaning easier.</p><p><i><b>Versatility:</b></i> Choose a vacuum that can easily transition from hard floors to carpets and upholstery.</p><p><i><b>Accessories:</b></i> Consider a vacuum that comes with a range of accessories, such as a crevice tool, dusting brush, and upholstery brush.</p><p><i><b>Filtration:</b></i> Look for a vacuum with a high-efficiency filtration system to capture small particles and improve air quality</p>
        </div>
    
